title.narrative: Urban Development and Poor Neighborhood Upgrading Project

description.narrative: The project development objectives are to: (1) improve access to infrastructure and basic services for people living in selected unplanned settlements in Brazzaville and Pointe Noire; and (2) strengthen government and municipal capacity for urban upgrading.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Accounting Software and Training | Description :The Borrower shall, no later than three (3) months from theEffective Date, install, within the PCU, a computerized financial management and accounting system satisfactory to the Bank andtrain the fiduciary staff in the use of the software. | Due Date :July 7, 2017

Finance Agreement :External Auditor | Description :The Borrower shall, no later than three (3) months after the Effective Date,recruit external auditors with qualifications, experience and terms of reference acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :July 7, 2017

Finance Agreement :Midterm Review | Description :The Borrower shall (a) carry out, no later than 30 months after the Effectivedate, a Midterm Review to assess the overall progress in implementation of the Project; (b) prepare and furnish to the Bank, atleast one (1) month prior to such review, a progress report on the implementation of the Project; and (c) review with the Bank suchreport, and take prompt measures required to ensure efficient | Due Date :18-Nov-2018

Finance Agreement :Procurement Training | Description :The Borrower shall, no later than three (3) months from the Effective Date,ensure the training of the PCU staff on World Bank procurement procedures, in specialized training institutions. | Due Date :July7,2017

Finance Agreement :Record Keeping | Description :The Borrower shall no later than six (3) months from the Effective Date, establishwithin the PCU, a Project records keeping system, satisfactory to the Bank, and train relevant staff. | Due Date :July 7, 2017

Finance Agreement :Staffing of PCU | Description :The Borrower shall, no later than three (3) months from the Effective Date,recruit a procurement specialist, an accountant, and a safeguards specialist, all with qualifications, experience and terms ofreference acceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :July 7, 2017

Finance Agreement :Task Force | Description :The Borrower shall, no later than 3 months after the Effective date, establish andmaintain a task force in the MCUDH, with composition and terms of reference acceptable to the Bank, to assist the PCU to assuretransfer of competences and provide adequate incentives for civil servants therein to participate fully in Project implementation.| Due Date : July 7, 2017
